<TITLE> 29-member recession taskforce to be announced </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 16(bdnews24.com)The government will constitute a 29-member task force to prepare Bangladesh's response to the global recession. Finance minister AMA Muhith told reporters on Monday that the body would comprise representatives of the three major parties, including the main opposition BNP, economists, specialists and businessmen. "The decision was taken at a cabinet meeting earlier today. The Prime Minister may announce it in parliament later today," said Muhith. bdnews
